# Trivy suppressions: not-affected (VEX) dispositions for the Green PM site.
#
# This is a static Astro site (astro.config.mjs: output: 'static'), built on
# Linux and deployed to GitHub Pages. It ships no server runtime and runs no
# dev server in production. Each CVE below is in a build-time, dev-server, or
# server-runtime code path that this deployment does not expose, so it is
# not-affected here rather than accepted-risk.
#
# Revisit and remove the relevant lines if the site ever adopts SSR, server
# islands, on-demand rendering, or is served by the Vite dev server in an
# untrusted setting. The proper long-term fix is to upgrade astro, vite, and
# js-yaml; that is a breaking major migration (astro 4 to 6+ removes
# @astrojs/tailwind) and requires npm access, tracked separately.

# astro: reflected XSS via server islands. Server islands are an SSR feature;
# a static build renders none.
CVE-2025-64764
# astro: reflected XSS via unescaped slot name. Server-render path only.
CVE-2026-50146
# astro: Host header SSRF in the prerendered error page fetch. Requires the
# Astro server runtime; the static build serves prerendered files with no fetch.
CVE-2026-54299
# vite: server.fs.deny bypass on Windows alternate data streams. Affects the
# Vite dev server only, is Windows-specific, and the build runs on Linux.
CVE-2026-53571
# js-yaml: denial of service via crafted YAML. A build-time dependency; no
# untrusted YAML is parsed at run time on the served static site.
CVE-2026-59869
